  "prompt": "Why do lots of people consider Ben Affleck an awful actor?",
  "response": "Ben Affleck's reputation as an actor has been a topic of debate among film critics and audiences. Several reasons might contribute to the perception that he is an \"awful\" actor:\n\n1. **High-Profile Failures**: Affleck has been part of several high-profile films that were critically panned, such as \"Gigli\" (2003) and \"Daredevil\" (2003). These movies received negative reviews and contributed to a negative public perception of his acting abilities.\n\n2. **Overexposure**: In the early 2000s, Affleck was highly visible in the media due to his high-profile relationship with Jennifer Lopez and his frequent appearances in both tabloids and films. This overexposure might have led to audience fatigue and increased scrutiny of his performances.\n\n3. **Range and Versatility**: Some critics argue that Affleck's range as an actor is limited. While he has received praise for certain roles, such as in \"Good Will Hunting\" (1997) and \"Argo\" (2012), his performances in other genres have been less well-received.\n\n4. **Public Perception and Media Narratives**: The media often plays a role in shaping public opinion. Negative reviews and media narratives can influence how an actor is perceived, even if their work is not objectively poor.\n\n5. **Comparison to Directing**: Affleck has found more critical success as a director than as an actor. His directorial efforts, like \"Argo\" and \"Gone Baby Gone\" (2007), have been well-received, which might lead some to focus more on his acting shortcomings.\n\nIt's important to note that opinions about actors are subjective, and while some people may consider Affleck an awful actor, others appreciate his work and recognize his contributions to film.",
